results.raw: Missing Therapy Dog Named Ladybug Found at 367 Grove St, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55101
results.title: Missing Therapy Dog Named Ladybug Found

nib.text:
Ladybug, the missing therapy dog, has been located and reunited with her owner, a U.S. Navy veteran.

According to an update from the St. Paul Police Department, someone spotted the Shar Pei, Pitbull, Retriever mix inside of a 2008 gray Dodge Caliber that was reported stolen and called 911.

Police arrived and arrested a 33-year-old woman who was inside the car with Ladybug.

The therapy dog was missing since Tuesday when her owner reported his car stolen with Ladybug inside.
